reviews.name: Cel W.
reviews.review: After driving into the garage and deciding I didn't have enough time to shop, I drove back out to exit. As I turned around I noticed a 5 car waiting line.Two out of the five had major issues trying to pay to exit the garage.One of them pushed the button for help and a very rude, demeaning and impatient lady was heard over the intercom speaking to the man waiting in the car to be let out. His card was not being read after inserting it multiple times. After waiting for five minutes, the lady finally let him out. When it came to my turn, I was being charged for sitting in my car waiting in line for 12 min. a total of $5.00.I pushed the button and explained to the lady that I had not parked, but had merely driven in and turned right back to exit-I did a "U-ey". She sarcastically asked what is a "U-ey"?If I was in the garage I had to have parked it.I explained what I did again and she (in a very demeaning and sarcastic tone) said you are either a pedestrian, in which you can walk out, or a car driver in which you have to pay. Then she asked what time does my card say I checked in?I stated 14:22 and the time was now 2:34. She exclaimed quite loudly over the intercom that I had been in there two hours and needed to pay. (Obviously she doesn't understand a 24 hour clock.)She then hung up the intercom. Frustratingly I buzzed the button again realizing she didn't understand the time and tried to explain, but she wouldn't let me out and started to yell over me.Incredible experience!

reviews.name: Ashley D.
reviews.review: This parking lot is a rip off. The worker is extremely disrespectful. Their sign clearly says $15 flat rate, yet I was charged $25. Their pay machine has instructions with steps 1-3. However, it's incorrect. 1st step says insert payment. I paid with card. Next step is choose your time. As soon as I inserted my card the machine read $20 until a certain time, but I only needed one hour. I was looking for where to adjust the time then suddenly it said "completing transaction". I quickly pushed "cancel", but next thing that shows up is "printing receipt". I explained to the worker what happened and he said it was my fault because I was with two other people and we were causing a shadow that blocked the machine. Which is complete bullsh*t. The machine is right next to the lighted office and there's plenty of street lights. I read the instructions perfectly fine. I have the picture to prove the instructions are not clear. He showed us that we were suppose to insert payment then click the small yellow button located on the bottom right. How is anyone suppose to know to click that when it's not stated anywhere on the machine? Plus the yellow button said for oversized vehicles. My car is not oversized. For step 1, there is a picture of three buttons that says $5, $15, $20. So we clicked $5 thinking it would just be $5, but instead it added $5 to the $20. When we asked the worker if anything could be done, so we wouldn't be charged $25 all he said was "you guys are good" as in we're ok

reviews.name: Brittany  B.
reviews.review:
ATTENTION: THIS PARKING GARAGE IS A SCAM!!! Do not go to this parking garage. It was right across from Pier 29 with "Public Parking" signs pointing to it. When I go to Pier 39, I usually park a few piers away to save money. I double and triple checked the sign to make sure there really was a "10 dollar flat rate" before four hours like we initially saw when we pulled into the garage. We saw nothing about having to get the ticket validated. Nothing other than the "10 dollar flat rate" that it claimed to have.

We make sure we get what we want to get done within four hours and make it back in time and lo and behold, we get charged 25 dollars! And then the scam artist of an employee said "Well there's a catch, you have to get it validated at the exploratorium for a 10 dollar flat rate." And he says otherwise it's 3 dollars every 30 minutes and then it caps out at 25 dollars. And considering we were back before four hours, that would be 24 dollars at the most if you do the math.

If you're going to charge something other than a flat rate, post that on the sign. And don't retrospectively make up a "3 dollars per every 30 minute rate" when, since I was only there for four hours, does not mathematically make sense. THIS PARKING LOT IS NOTHING BUT A SCAM. Park elsewhere unless you feel like getting robbed even more than you already do in San Francisco. L

reviews.review: The WORST place to park. They overpack the lot. It is an emergency hazard. They park cars behind other cars, blocking you in. Then, those who leave their keys are leaving their cars in the hands of CRAZY drivers. Sketchy as hell! And it cost $40 for just a couple hours.

reviews.name: G W.
reviews.review: DONT PARK HERE!!!!! THEY DONT HAVE SECURITY AT NIGHT!!! MY CAR WAS BURGLARIZED AND THEY DONT WANT TO TAKE RESPONSIBILITY

reviews.name: Haley B.
reviews.review: Horrible experience! Got our car window busted out and we were only there for 30 minutes. About 8-10 cars all got busted windows, some had things stolen. Tried to call police but it is private property so they wouldnt come out. No cameras. Do. Not. Park. Your. Vehicle. Here. Thankfully we had insurance.

reviews.name: Nick N.
reviews.review: maybe in San Francisco it's normal, but for the first time I have such a surprise when you paid for a night parking, arrived in the morning, and the car is all broken, and no one is responsible for it, because in San Francisco it's normal, so before  how to get out of the car, make sure it is under surveillance

reviews.name: Marie B.
reviews.review: I waited in line for 30 minutes to get near the garage and saw its $20 not $15.  Whatever not a big deal.  Get to the attendant after now almost 45 minutes waiting are told that its cash only and are turned away.  Is anything said on this website true? Very disappointed

reviews.name: Jay C.
reviews.review: Don't park in that garage. They smashed they windows of my rental car last week. This is a very dangerous place. No security at all. If you do park in there don't leave any valuables in your car please.

reviews.name: Julia V.
reviews.review: This is the worst parking garage experience Ive ever had. From the beginning, the attendant who claimed to be the manager was extremely rude and unprofessional. I bought a parking spot from the Spot Hero app, which clearly states in the reservation any free spot that does not say reserved is available. The manager wanted us to park in the middle of the entry way sticking out, and not in a spot. I showed him the Spot Hero app that clearly states we paid for a spot and there are no refunds once the time has stated,  he said I dont care if you cancel it dont talk to me. Upon arriving back to the car, the drivers window was completely smashed in. I RECOMMEND DO NOT PARK HERE. It is better to pay a little more than to have an experience like this.

reviews.name: Rhina C.
reviews.review: Not enough space to explain what happened. But I drove into this parking lot on 12/28/19 about 7:30pm.  I had a very awful (scary) experience with the parking attendant.  I parked and asked the attendant at what time the lot closed and he walked away and mumbled something, so I said excuse me I didnt hear u & restated my question.  He YELLED  it back.   I said dont be an asshole! (I asked to make sure we didnt come to close to closing time)The guy lungged at me as if he was going to assault me.  My 15 yr old son stepped in front of me to protect me.  The guy lungged at him.  I told the attendant ur not going to hurt my son!   The other parking attendants came and was yelling at their coworker.  One of the men gave me back my money and apologized.  I said whats wrong with this guy.  He told me he couldnt do anything because that guy was the one in charge.  I heard the name Marmoot.  I dont know if thats his name.  I was afraid for my sons & my safety.  After that, I wasnt going to leave my car there. He continued yelling saying that he was going to have my car towed.  I Looked for a sign with the parking company info.  I got in my car to leave.  One of the attendants helped me get out.  I was afraid of him following me to mess up my car or hurt us.  This was scary for my son & I.  I hope this doesnt have to happen to anyone again.  This man seemed as if he were drugged.  His behavior was erratic.

reviews.name: Mary T.
reviews.review: It was a weekend and although the sign said $30, they charged $40 since ours is a truck. But our other members of the group were charged $40 also for small cars because they said the $30 price is only fir parking up to 3:00pm. They only took cash. I think we were scammed. It is false advertising and they can be in a heap of trouble. I work with plenty of lawyers! Also, they take your car keys and park your car for you. We felt uncomfortable leaving strangers with our keys since they dont wear uniform shirts to distinguish from anyone off the street. Then upon returning we had to wait in line to pick up our vehicles! Better to park in another lot next time. They cost the same and safer/ more convenient.

reviews.name: Sam J.
reviews.review: Advertises 20 all day, then says its 30. Operator extremely rude.

reviews.name: Karla B.
reviews.review: Terrible service. My car was scratched when I picked it up, they did not take responsibility, and the guys became aggressive and threatening. Extremely frustrating. Please beware!

reviews.name: Erin P.
reviews.review: DO NOT PARK HERE!!! CAR WAS BROKEN INTO AND NO ATTENDENT ON DUTY WHEN I CAME TO PICK UP MY CAR

reviews.name: B R.
reviews.review: DO NOT PARK HERE, VERY UNSAFE.  We were in the area on business and not at all familiar with the Pier 39 area.  Our GPS suggested this parking location; which is public.  We paid the attendant and went over for a quick dinner.  We returned to our car before 9:00 p.m., no attendant to be found and car had been broken into and our bags (which had been secured)had been stolen and another group told us their car had also been broken into.  Unless your IDs are stolen the police will only take a report over the phone for insurance purposes, otherwise you are basically out of luck. The police said this happens 2-3 times a night in this location, but yet there is no attendant, no cameras, no signs posted that the attendant will be gone at a certain time or that it is a high crime area, no security guards or even police patrolling. If you decide to park here DO NOT leave anything of value, sentimental, or hard/expensive to replace. We were also told these criminals know how to look for tourist/rental cars to target since they would likely have luggage or valuable in them and not likely to return to the area if there was every a chance they were prosecuted. BEWARE, this is a systematic process. What these criminals stole from us wasn't worth near what it is costing in time and expense to replace it.

reviews.name: Michael H.
reviews.review:
SP+ Parking (1282 Embarcadero)...

DO NOT PARK HERE!!!!! Sept 27, 2022. Parked car at 1210...Did Alcatraz tour at 1230....Came back at 315 and back window was busted out. All luggage, purses, cash, etc. GONE!!!! After seeing the other reviews, this is obviously a "smash and grab" place. Other out of state cars were also broken-into....ON THE SAME DAY!

No mobile security, no CCTV, no staff!

After the fact, we looked at reviews and see the same experience has been happening to people for years!!

Called police 4 times and no one came, we were told to physically go to the police station.

reviews.name: Elaine A.
reviews.review: No attendant on duty here. We purchased a pass online. Noticed we had a wrong number for our rental car license when we got to the parking lot. We purchased another pass so our car wouldnt be towed or fined. Sent an email and havent heard anything from them. Got an automatic email right away that they would contact us soon. Its been almost a week.

reviews.name: Ro M.
reviews.review: We had a TERRIBLE experience in this parking lot.  We parked to go to Alcatraz here and when we returned a few hours later, our two back cargo windows were busted out and our luggage was stolen.  NO ONE was onsite to help us.  NO ONE was watching your auto, at all.  We lost all of our luggage and the rental suffered damage, as well.  We spent the rest of the day in the police station.  Do NOT Park here.

reviews.name: Anna W.
reviews.review: Our car was broken into during the 3.5 hours we were touring Alcatraz. There was no lot attendant when we returned to the car around 7pm and our back windows with smashed in. For $26, I would expect at least a warning that break ins were common in the area.

reviews.review: parking about 4 hours
